30// V8FileLogger is used for collecting logging information from V8 during
31// execution. The result is dumped to a file.
32//
33// Available command line flags:
34//
35// --log
36// Minimal logging (no API, code, or GC sample events), default is off.
37//
38// --log-all
39// Log all events to the file, default is off. This is the same as combining
40// --log-api and --log-code.
41//
42// --log-api
43// Log API events to the logfile, default is off. --log-api implies --log.
44//
45// --log-code
46// Log code (create, move, and delete) events to the logfile, default is off.
47// --log-code implies --log.
48//
49// --logfile <filename>
50// Specify the name of the logfile, default is "v8.log".
51//
52// --prof
53// Collect statistical profiling information (ticks), default is off. The
54// tick profiler requires code events, so --prof implies --log-code.
55//
56// --prof-sampling-interval <microseconds>
57// The interval between --prof samples, default is 1000 microseconds (5000 on
58// Android).
59
60// Forward declarations.

62class Isolate;
63class JitLogger;
64class LogFile;
65class LowLevelLogger;

76#undef LOG
77#define LOG(isolate, Call) \
78 do { \
79 if (v8::internal::v8_flags.log) (isolate)->v8_file_logger()->Call; \
80 } while (false)
81
82#define LOG_CODE_EVENT(isolate, Call) \
83 do { \
84 auto&& logger = (isolate)->v8_file_logger(); \
85 if (logger->is_listening_to_code_events()) logger->Call; \
86 } while (false)

247 V8_NOINLINE V8_PRESERVE_MOST static void CallEventLoggerInternal(
248 Isolate* isolate, const char* name, v8::LogEventStatus se,
249 bool expose_to_api) {
250 LOG(isolate, TimerEvent(se, name));
251 if (V8_UNLIKELY(isolate->event_logger())) {
252 isolate->event_logger()(name, se);
253 }
254 }
255
256 V8_INLINE static void CallEventLogger(Isolate* isolate, const char* name,
257 v8::LogEventStatus se,
258 bool expose_to_api) {
259 if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.log_timer_events)) {
260 CallEventLoggerInternal(isolate, name, se, expose_to_api);
261 }

396 class TimerEvent##TimerName : public AllStatic { \
397 public: \
398 static const char* name(void* unused = nullptr) { \
399 return "V8." #TimerName; \
400 } \
401 static bool expose_to_api() { return expose; } \
402 };
